subSubSection.paragraph:
Within the 
Clivinini
. the subtribe 
Ardistomina
is characterized as follows: Elytron latero-distally (
Fig. 22
) with a plica (
ep
) and an adjacent abdominal (segment VII) pleural projection (
app
) that together form an elytral-abdominal locking mechanism; ovipositor (
Figs 27-30
) with an asetose quadranguloid laterotergite, and unsegmented gonocoxa bearing at apex few long setae.

Labium:
In form, the mentum (
m
) is markedly to slightly transverse (L/W 0.43-0.56) among the clivinine genera (
Figs 17A-21A
); among the ardistomine genera (
Figs 13A-16A
) the mentum is slightly transverse to slightly elongate (L/W 0.57-0.95), a morphocline being 
Aspidoglossa-Semiardistomis-Ardistomis
.

Labial palpomere 3 (
lp3
) is elongate and fusiform in the 
Ardistomina
(
Figs 13A-16A
). This sclerite varies in the clivinines: fusiform in 

Clivina

(
Fig. 17A
), and variously widened in the remaining clivinine exemplar genera (
Figs 18A-21A
).
